{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T06:48:51.509Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"chain rule in networks"},{"type":"text","text":" is the mathematical principle that enables "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"backpropagation"},{"type":"text","text":" to compute gradients efficiently in deep neural networks. It allows us to determine how changing any single weight affects the final loss by breaking the computation into a chain of simpler, local derivatives through each layer."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What the Chain Rule Is (Mathematically)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For a simple composition of functions "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"y = f(g(x))"}},{"type":"text","text":", the chain rule states:"}]},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\frac{dy}{dx} = \\frac{df}{dg} \\cdot \\frac{dg}{dx}"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In neural networks with "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"n"}},{"type":"text","text":" nested layers, we need the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"multivariate chain rule"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial x} = \\sum_{i} \\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial u_i} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial u_i}{\\partial x}"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"where "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"L"}},{"type":"text","text":" is the loss and "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"u_i"}},{"type":"text","text":" are intermediate variables."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Matters in Backpropagation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Neural networks are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"computation graphs"},{"type":"text","text":" where:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Forward pass"},{"type":"text","text":": values flow from input → hidden layers → output → loss\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Backward pass"},{"type":"text","text":": gradients flow from loss → output → hidden layers → weights"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The chain rule lets us compute gradients by "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"multiplying local derivatives"},{"type":"text","text":" at each node as we propagate backward. Without it, we couldn't train deep networks because we wouldn't know how to adjust weights."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Crucial insight"},{"type":"text","text":": Backpropagation is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"repeated application of the chain rule"},{"type":"text","text":" combined with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"dynamic programming"},{"type":"text","text":" to cache intermediate gradients, avoiding exponential recomputation."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How It Works: Concrete Example"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider a 2-layer network:"}]},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"h = \\sigma(W_1 x), \\quad \\hat{y} = W_2 h, \\quad L = \\text{loss}(\\hat{y}, y)"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"To compute "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial W_1}"}},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Forward pass"},{"type":"text","text":": compute "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"h"}},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\hat{y}"}},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"L"}}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Backward pass"},{"type":"text","text":" (chain rule):"}]}]}]},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial W_1} = \n\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial \\hat{y}} \\cdot\n\\frac{\\partial \\hat{y}}{\\partial h} \\cdot\n\\frac{\\partial h}{\\partial W_1}"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each term is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"local derivative"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial \\hat{y}}"}},{"type":"text","text":": from loss function (e.g., MSE or cross-entropy)\n- "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\frac{\\partial \\hat{y}}{\\partial h} = W_2"}},{"type":"text","text":": linear layer derivative\n- "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\frac{\\partial h}{\\partial W_1} = \\sigma'(W_1 x) \\cdot x"}},{"type":"text","text":": activation derivative times input"}]},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"For a deep network with  layers, this becomes:\n\\[\n\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial W_k} = \\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial y} \\cdot \\prod_{j=n}^{k+1} \\frac{\\partial h_j}{\\partial h{j-1}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial h{k+1}}{\\partial W_k}\n\\]"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each gradient is the product of sensitivities along the path from "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"W_k"}},{"type":"text","text":" to the loss."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Chain Rule vs. Backpropagation: Key Distinction"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Concept"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain rule"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The calculus theorem for composing derivatives"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Backpropagation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An algorithm that applies the chain rule in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"reverse mode"},{"type":"text","text":" + caches intermediate results"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Backpropagation is not just the chain rule\" because it adds "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"dynamic programming"},{"type":"text","text":": we compute and store "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial h_j}"}},{"type":"text","text":" once, then use it for all weights in layer "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"j"}},{"type":"text","text":", avoiding recomputation."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without caching, naive chain rule application would produce formulas growing "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"exponentially"},{"type":"text","text":" with depth. Backprop keeps complexity "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"linear"},{"type":"text","text":" in the number of operations."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Role in Automatic Differentiation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Automatic differentiation (Autodiff)"},{"type":"text","text":" is the general framework implementing backpropagation:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mode"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use case"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Chain rule direction"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Forward mode"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Few inputs, many outputs"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Forward: computes "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial x_i}"}},{"type":"text","text":" for one input direction"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reverse mode"},{"type":"text","text":" (backprop)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Many inputs (weights), few outputs (loss)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Backward: computes all "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial w_i}"}},{"type":"text","text":" in one pass"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Neural networks have millions of weights but one loss, so "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"reverse-mode autodiff"},{"type":"text","text":" is essential."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of a neural network as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"pipeline"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Forward"},{"type":"text","text":": water flows input → output → loss"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Backward"},{"type":"text","text":": you ask \"how much does a leak at this pipe affect the final amount?\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain rule"},{"type":"text","text":": multiply the \"sensitivity\" at each stage along the path"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each weight's gradient = product of sensitivities from that weight to the loss."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The chain rule decomposes complex derivatives into products of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"local derivatives"},{"type":"text","text":" at each network node"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Backpropagation = "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"reverse-mode autodiff"},{"type":"text","text":" applying the chain rule backward with caching"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without the chain rule, we couldn't compute gradients in deep networks → no training with gradient descent"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Backprop's computational cost is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"linear"},{"type":"text","text":" in operations; naive chain rule would be "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"exponential"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is why deep learning works: the chain rule makes training networks with millions of parameters computationally feasible."}]}]}}
